**Min Pooling Layer (`MinPool2d`)**:  - Increase kernel size (k). This expands receptive field allowing more context information extraction from neighboring pixels thereby enhancing edge detection capabilities.<br>   <p/> **Hyperparameter:** Kernel Size ``KS`` < br>. </div></li><ul style="padding :0;">



---




 -- Max pooling layer --







In general max pool layers reduce spatial dimensions but preserve feature maps' channels; however increasing number filters per channel enhances object localization abilities thus benefiting downstream tasks like classification. Increasing filter numbers comes at cost computational overhead therefore balancing tradeoffs is crucial.**






# Conclusion





Overall these suggested alterations improve both min &amp maximumpooling operations enabling better capture features leading ultimately improved network efficacy without compromising essential functionalities implemented initially..

