## Proposed Modification #0 - Dynamically Scalable GAVG Pooling (DS-G AVG)**   





### Key Insight : The conventional global average pooling operation is static based on predefined kernel size which limits adaptability against varying data dimensions. To overcome such limitation, I propose dynamically scaling Gaussian averaging kernels according object spatial dimensionalities using adaptive convolution techniques like Dilated Convolutions.(Dilations allow increasing receptive fields without changing network architecture.)







